-- Liverpool May Bid $15 Million for Tottenham’s Defoe, Mirror Says: Roundup
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2012-01-16T10:40:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-16/liverpool-may-bid-15-million-for-tottenham-s-defoe-mirror-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Defoe Liverpool Bound?  Liverpool may offer Tottenham as much as 10 million pounds
($15.3 million) for striker  Jermain Defoe , the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  Bolton Chasing Dos Santos  Bolton manager Owen Coyle may put a 4 million pound bid in
for Tottenham winger Giovani dos Santos, the  Daily Mirror 
reported. A 3.4 million pound bid for the 22-year-old by Spanish
club Sevilla was turned down.  City Close to Pozo Deal  Manchester City is close to signing 15-year-old Real Madrid
strike Jose Angel Pozo for 3.5 million pounds, the  Daily Mail 
reported. Pozo is expected to sign a five-year deal on March 15,
the day he turns 16, the paper said.  Redknapp Scouting Remy  Tottenham manager Harry Redknapp has flown to France twice
to see Marseille’s forward Loic Remy play, the  Sun  reported. The
25-year-old has been valued at 15 million pounds by the French
club.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Danielle Rossingh in  London  at 
 drossingh@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
